# Trivy vulnerability suppressions
# Review monthly and remove entries when upstream fixes are available.

# rclone v1.73.2 built with grpc v1.76.0 — fix requires grpc v1.79.3.
# Waiting for rclone upstream to update. Authorization bypass via missing
# leading slash in :path — rclone doesn't expose gRPC services.
CVE-2026-33186

# rclone/lazygit: jsonparser DoS via crafted JSON input.
# These are CLI tools in sandboxed container, not processing untrusted JSON.
GHSA-6g7g-w4f8-9c9x
CVE-2026-32285

# lazygit v0.60.0 built with Go 1.25.x — may still need Go 1.25.8+ for fix.
# Risk: crypto/tls session resumption — lazygit doesn't expose TLS services.
CVE-2025-68121

# Go stdlib URL parsing / HTML meta tag injection in rclone/lazygit.
# These are CLI tools in sandboxed container, not processing untrusted URLs.
CVE-2026-25679
CVE-2026-27142

# node-tar transitive dependency in globally-installed npm CLIs
# (@anthropic-ai/claude-code, @openai/codex, @google/gemini-cli, opencode-ai).
# These CLIs don't process untrusted tar archives at runtime.
# Fix available (tar 7.5.3-7.5.8) but upstream packages haven't updated.
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960

# glob/minimatch transitive deps in globally-installed npm CLIs.
# glob 10.4.5 command injection requires malicious filenames — CLIs don't
# process user-controlled filenames in glob context.
# minimatch 9.0.5-9.0.6 DoS via crafted patterns — CLIs use hardcoded patterns.
CVE-2025-64756
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# Debian bookworm base image system libraries — no fixes available in bookworm.
# These are in system packages, not directly exposed to untrusted input.

# libexpat1 2.5.0-1+deb12u2: integer overflow causing information disclosure / data integrity issues
# Transitive dep of git, python3, etc. No fixed version in bookworm. No XML parsing of untrusted input.
CVE-2026-25210

# glibc 2.36-9+deb12u13: integer overflow in memalign (heap corruption)
# Container runs trusted code only; no user-controlled allocation sizes.
CVE-2026-0861

# glibc 2.36-9+deb12u13: DoS via iconv() function
# No fix in bookworm (fix_deferred). Container doesn't process untrusted charset conversions.
CVE-2026-4046

# git 2.39.5: arbitrary code execution + arbitrary file writes
# Container git is used by AI agents in sandboxed workspace. Users control their own repos.
CVE-2025-48384
CVE-2025-48385

# openldap libldap 2.5.13: null pointer dereference in ber_memalloc_x
# Container doesn't use LDAP; libldap is a transitive dependency.
CVE-2023-2953

# mbedtls 2.28.3: use-after-free, integer overflow, NULL deref, AESNI race condition
# Container doesn't use mbedtls directly; it's a dependency of rclone/curl.
CVE-2025-47917
CVE-2024-23775
CVE-2025-48965
CVE-2025-52496

# mbedtls 2.28.3: TLS 1.3 client impersonation, buffer overflow RCE, FFDH shared secret manipulation
# Container doesn't use mbedtls directly; it's a dependency of rclone/curl. No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-34873
CVE-2026-34875
CVE-2026-34872

# sqlite 3.40.1: integer overflow
# SQLite is used by OpenCode for local DB only (no untrusted SQL input).
CVE-2025-7458

# p7zip 16.02: ZIP directory traversal (RCE)
# p7zip is used by yazi for archive preview only on user-owned files.
CVE-2025-11001
CVE-2025-11002

# zlib 1.2.13: integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64 (will_not_fix in bookworm)
# Only affects minizip API for creating ZIP files — container doesn't create ZIPs.
CVE-2023-45853

# p7zip 16.02: integer underflow in Ppmd7.c (no fix in Debian bookworm)
# p7zip is used by yazi for archive preview only on user-owned files.
CVE-2023-31102

# docker/cli v29.0.3 bundled in gh CLI: local privilege escalation via plugin search path
# gh CLI is a dev tool inside sandboxed container — no Docker daemon present.
CVE-2025-15558

# node-tar 7.5.7: hardlink/symlink path traversal via drive-relative linkpath
# CLIs don't process untrusted tar archives at runtime.
GHSA-qffp-2rhf-9h96
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# cpython 3.11 (Debian bookworm): python3 added for ECC observe hooks (stdlib only).
# No network services, no untrusted input — hooks run locally on tool-use events.
# http.client buffering DoS
CVE-2025-13836
# IMAP command injection
CVE-2025-15366
# POP3 command injection
CVE-2025-15367
# python-markdown DoS via malformed HTML
CVE-2025-69534
# tarfile infinite loop
CVE-2025-8194
# email header injection via unquoted newlines
CVE-2026-1299

# systemd 252.39 (libsystemd0, libudev1): privilege escalation via RegisterMachine D-Bus method
# Container doesn't use machined/RegisterMachine; no fix available in bookworm.
CVE-2026-4105

# openssh-client 9.2p1: GSSAPI information disclosure / DoS
# Container uses SSH only for git clone over SSH (not GSSAPI); no fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-3497

# openssh-client 9.2p1: scp privilege escalation via legacy protocol
# Container uses git over HTTPS, not scp; no fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-35385

# openssh-client 9.2p1: security bypass via mishandling
# Container uses git over HTTPS, not SSH auth; no fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-35414

# picomatch 4.0.3: ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns (CVE-2026-33671)
# Transitive dep of globally-installed npm CLIs. CLIs use hardcoded glob patterns,
# not user-controlled input. Fix: 4.0.4 — waiting for upstream CLI updates.
CVE-2026-33671

# ncurses 6.4-4: buffer overflow in ncurses (CVE-2025-69720)
# System library in Debian bookworm, no fix available. Terminal usage only.
CVE-2025-69720

# cpython 3.11: command-line option injection in webbrowser.open()
# Container doesn't use webbrowser.open(); python3 is for ECC hooks only.
CVE-2026-4519

# libnghttp2-14: DoS via malformed HTTP/2 frames after session termination
# System library in Debian bookworm, no fix available. Container doesn't expose HTTP/2 services.
CVE-2026-27135

# systemd (libsystemd0, libudev1): arbitrary code execution via spurious IPC
# Container doesn't use systemd IPC; no fix available in bookworm.
CVE-2026-29111

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.2 / lazygit v0.60.0: chain building work amplification
# These are CLI tools in sandboxed container, not exposed to untrusted certificate chains.
CVE-2026-32280

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.2 / lazygit v0.60.0: Root.Chmod symlink traversal
# Container runs trusted code only; these tools don't use Root.Chmod on untrusted paths.
CVE-2026-32282

# jq 1.6: out-of-bounds read in jv_parse_sized() on malformed input
# jq processes trusted JSON from entrypoint scripts and hooks, not user-controlled input. No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-39979

# jq 1.6: DoS via crafted JSON object
# Same as above — jq only processes trusted entrypoint/hook JSON. No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-40164

# jq 1.6 / libjq1: DoS or potential arbitrary code execution via malformed JSON
# jq only processes trusted entrypoint/hook JSON. No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-32316

# cpython 3.11: arbitrary code execution or information disclosure
# python3 is used for ECC observe hooks only (stdlib, no network, no untrusted input). No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-6100

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.2 / lazygit v0.60.0: crypto/x509 DoS via inefficient cert chain validation
# These are CLI tools in sandboxed container, not exposed to untrusted certificate chains.
CVE-2026-32281

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.2 / lazygit v0.60.0: TLS DoS via multiple key update messages
# Container doesn't expose TLS endpoints; these tools make outbound TLS only to trusted services.
CVE-2026-32283

# rclone 1.73.5: unauthorized access via unauthenticated Remote Control endpoint
# Container does not run `rclone rcd` or use `--rc` flag; only `rclone bisync` for R2 sync.
# Remote Control endpoint is not exposed. No fixed version available upstream.
CVE-2026-41176

# rclone 1.73.5: unauthenticated local command execution via exposed RC endpoint
# Same as above — RC endpoint is not enabled in this container.
CVE-2026-41179

# libgcrypt20 1.10.1-3: DoS and buffer overflow via crafted ECDH ciphertext
# System library transitive dep; container does not process untrusted ECDH ciphertext.
# No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-41989

# libcap2 1:2.66-4+deb12u2+b2: privilege escalation via TOCTOU race in
# cap_set_file(). System library used during container init only — no
# application code path passes untrusted paths to cap_set_file. The race
# requires local file-access on the same filesystem, which doesn't exist
# as a multi-tenant boundary in the sandboxed container model.
# No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-4878

# libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6: DTLS DoS via zero-length fragment.
# Container does not expose any DTLS/UDP TLS service; GnuTLS is linked
# by CLI tools (curl, wget) for outbound HTTPS only. The vulnerable
# DTLS server path is never reached.
# No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-33845

# libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6: GnuTLS DoS via heap buffer overflow.
# Same package and exposure profile as CVE-2026-33845: GnuTLS is linked
# by CLI tools (curl, wget) for outbound HTTPS only — no DTLS/UDP TLS
# service is exposed and the vulnerable code path requires server-side
# TLS handling that the container never performs.
# No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-33846

# openssh-client 1:9.2p1-2+deb12u9: arbitrary command execution via shell
# metacharacters in username. Codeflare uses git-over-HTTPS exclusively
# (rules/cloudflare-environment.md: "Git over HTTPS only, no SSH keys"),
# so the openssh-client binary is installed but not invoked. The exploit
# path requires the user to ssh somewhere with attacker-controlled
# username, which doesn't happen in the codeflare workflow.
# No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-35386

# libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6: policy bypass via case-sensitive nameConstraints
# comparison. GnuTLS is linked by CLI tools (curl, wget) for outbound HTTPS
# only; the container does not act as a TLS server validating client certs
# against name constraints. No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-3833

# libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6: authentication bypass via NUL character in
# username. Container does not run any authenticator that reads usernames
# through GnuTLS APIs; outbound HTTPS only. No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-42010

# libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6: security bypass via incorrect name constraint
# handling. Same exposure as CVE-2026-3833 - outbound HTTPS only, no TLS
# server role. No fix available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-42011

# libgnutls30 3.7.9-2+deb12u6: DoS via DTLS packet reordering. Container does
# not expose any DTLS endpoint (no DTLS server, no DTLS client), and GnuTLS
# is only loaded as a transitive dep of curl/libcurl which speaks HTTPS over
# TCP only. Same exposure profile as the other gnutls entries above. No fix
# available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-42009

# libmbedcrypto7 / libmbedtls14 / libmbedx509-1 (mbedtls 2.28.3): seed misuse
# in HMAC_DRBG / CTR_DRBG. Container does not use mbedtls directly; transitive
# dep of rclone/curl. No DRBG-derived material is exposed. No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-25835

# libssh2-1 1.10.0-3+b1: integer overflow via large username/password.
# Container uses git-over-HTTPS exclusively (no SSH); libssh2 is linked but
# never invoked with user-controlled credentials. No fix available in Debian
# bookworm.
CVE-2026-7598

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.x (Go 1.26.2) and lazygit v0.60.0 (Go 1.25.7):
# new batch of HIGH stdlib advisories. Fixes are in Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3 but
# rclone/lazygit upstream releases have not rebuilt yet. Exposure profile is
# unchanged from prior Go stdlib entries above: both binaries are CLI tools
# in the sandboxed container, do outbound network only, and do not parse
# untrusted addresses, NUL-byte hostnames, HTTP/2 SETTINGS frames as a
# server, or untrusted email phrases.
#
# CVE-2026-33811: net.LookupCNAME with cgo DNS resolver miscounts answers.
# CVE-2026-33814: HTTP/2 SETTINGS frame handling enters error state on peer input.
# CVE-2026-39820: ParseAddress / ParseAddressList input handling DoS.
# CVE-2026-39836: Dial / LookupPort panic when hostname contains NUL byte.
# CVE-2026-42499: net/mail consumePhrase DoS on pathological inputs.
CVE-2026-33811
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39820
CVE-2026-39836
CVE-2026-42499

# curl / libcurl3-gnutls / libcurl4 7.88.1-10+deb12u14: wrong file transfer
# due to incorrect SMB connection reuse. Container uses curl exclusively for
# outbound HTTPS (git-over-HTTPS, package fetches); the SMB protocol is not
# invoked and no SMB URLs are ever constructed. No fix available in Debian
# bookworm.
CVE-2026-5773

# curl / libcurl3-gnutls / libcurl4 7.88.1-10+deb12u14: information disclosure
# via cookie leak when reusing connections with different credentials. Same
# exposure profile as CVE-2026-5773 above: container uses curl exclusively for
# outbound HTTPS to fixed, trusted endpoints (GitHub raw, PyPI, deb mirrors).
# No multi-tenant cookie state, no untrusted-host reuse. No fix in bookworm.
CVE-2026-6276

# libexpat1 2.5.0-1+deb12u2: computational complexity on crafted XML attribute
# names (DoS). Transitive dep of git, python3, etc. Container parses no
# untrusted XML at runtime - same exposure profile as the existing
# CVE-2026-25210 entry above. No fixed version in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-45186

# go-git/go-billy/v5 v5.6.2 embedded in lazygit v0.60.0 binary: path traversal
# in symlink-followed file operations. Fixed in v5.9.0; lazygit upstream has
# not yet rebuilt with the patched go-billy. lazygit runs only against the
# user's own git working trees (trusted local repos cloned via HTTPS); it
# never operates on attacker-controlled bundles or remote-driven symlinks.
# Exposure profile is identical to the other "Go stdlib / module in
# rclone/lazygit binaries" entries above.
CVE-2026-44973

# Go stdlib in rclone / lazygit binaries (Go 1.25.1 build): new batch of
# DoS-class advisories. Fixes are in Go 1.24.x / 1.25.x point releases but
# rclone/lazygit upstream releases have not rebuilt. Exposure profile is
# identical to the earlier Go stdlib entries above: both binaries are CLI
# tools in the sandboxed container, do outbound network only, and never
# parse untrusted tar/zip archives, query parameters, or untrusted cert
# chains as a server.
#
# CVE-2025-58183: archive/tar unbounded allocation when parsing GNU sparse map.
# CVE-2025-61726: net/url memory exhaustion in query-parameter parsing.
# CVE-2025-61728: archive/zip excessive CPU when building zip with many entries.
# CVE-2025-61729: crypto/x509 DoS via excessive work on crafted chains.
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61729

# gomarkdown/markdown v0.0.0-20250810172220 embedded in a third-party
# CLI binary (transitive dep). Container does not feed user-controlled
# markdown to this library; the affected code path is only reachable
# when rendering attacker-supplied markdown, which the CLI never does.
# Upstream fix exists (v0.0.0-20260411013819) but the consuming CLI
# has not yet rebuilt.
CVE-2026-40890

# cpython 3.11 (libpython3.11-minimal 3.11.2-6+deb12u7): xml.parsers.expat
# and xml.etree.ElementTree DoS via crafted XML. python3 is added for ECC
# observe hooks (stdlib only); the container parses no untrusted XML at
# runtime. Same exposure profile as the existing CVE-2025-69534 entry.
# No fixed version available in Debian bookworm.
CVE-2026-7210

# libexpat1 2.5.0-1+deb12u2: large dynamic memory allocation in
# Expat XML parser leading to DoS via crafted XML input. Status:
# will_not_fix in Debian bookworm (no patched version available).
# The container's libexpat consumers (rclone, perl modules, system
# tooling) never parse attacker-controlled XML at runtime: rclone
# parses our own R2 ListObjects XML responses; perl is invoked only
# by codeflare-managed scripts. Same rationale as the cpython expat
# entries above (CVE-2026-7210, CVE-2025-69534).
CVE-2025-59375

# krb5 1.20.1-2+deb12u5 (libgssapi-krb5-2, libk5crypto3, libkrb5-3,
# libkrb5support0): DoS via integer underflow in GSS-API context
# establishment. Status: affected, no patched Debian bookworm package.
# Codeflare does not use Kerberos auth; krb5 ships transitively via
# libcurl / system tooling and is never invoked by any container code
# path. No attacker can reach the vulnerable GSS-API surface.
CVE-2026-40356

# Go stdlib net/netip in rclone v1.73.x / lazygit v0.60.0 (Go 1.25.1 build):
# Parse permits values other than IPv6 addresses. These CLI tools do not parse
# untrusted IP address input. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2; upstream not rebuilt.
CVE-2025-47912

# Go stdlib crypto/x509 in rclone / lazygit: maliciously crafted DER payload
# causes unbounded memory allocation. CLI tools in sandboxed container, not
# exposed to untrusted certificate chains. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-58185

# Go stdlib net/http in rclone / lazygit: HTTP/1 chunked body bypasses the
# default 1MB header limit. Container doesn't expose HTTP servers; these tools
# make outbound requests only. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-58186

# Go stdlib crypto/x509 in rclone / lazygit: name constraint checking DoS via
# crafted cert chain. CLI tools in sandboxed container, not exposed to untrusted
# certificate chains. Fix: Go 1.24.9 / 1.25.3.
CVE-2025-58187

# Go stdlib crypto/x509 in rclone / lazygit: DSA public key validation DoS via
# crafted cert chain. Same exposure as CVE-2025-58187 - no untrusted cert chains.
# Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-58188

# Go stdlib crypto/tls in rclone / lazygit: ALPN negotiation failure leaks
# connection state. Container doesn't expose TLS endpoints; outbound TLS only
# to trusted services. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-58189

# Go stdlib encoding/json in rclone / lazygit: processing time for invalid inputs
# scales poorly (DoS). CLI tools in sandboxed container, not processing untrusted
# JSON input at scale. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-61723

# Go stdlib net/http in rclone / lazygit: ReadResponse constructs unbounded
# response objects. Container doesn't expose HTTP servers; outbound only to
# trusted endpoints. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-61724

# Go stdlib net/mail in rclone / lazygit: ParseAddress domain-literal DoS via
# crafted input. CLI tools don't parse untrusted email addresses. Fix: Go 1.24.8 / 1.25.2.
CVE-2025-61725

# Go stdlib crypto/x509 in rclone / lazygit: excluded subdomain constraint
# bypass in cert chain validation. CLI tools in sandboxed container, not exposed
# to untrusted certificate chains. Fix: Go 1.24.11 / 1.25.5.
CVE-2025-61727

# perl-modules-5.36 (Debian bookworm): Archive::Tar extracts symlinks with
# attacker-controlled targets outside the extraction directory (symlink traversal
# in _make_special_file). Impact: NONE - container does not extract untrusted tar
# archives; perl is invoked only by codeflare-managed entrypoint scripts and
# system package tooling. No fix available in Debian bookworm (requires Perl 5.38+
# with Archive::Tar 3.08).
CVE-2026-42496

# perl-modules-5.36 / libperl5.36 (Debian bookworm): Archive::Tar before 3.10
# allows memory exhaustion via crafted tar archives. Impact: NONE - container
# does not extract untrusted tar archives; perl is invoked only by
# codeflare-managed entrypoint scripts and system package tooling. No fix
# available in Debian bookworm (requires Archive::Tar 3.10).
CVE-2026-9538

# perl-modules-5.36 (Debian bookworm): heap buffer overflow in Perl_study_chunk
# (regcomp_study.c) when compiling regex with large quantified fixed substrings
# on 32-bit builds - mincount * length overflows SSize_t, undersizing SvGROW.
# Impact: NONE - container is 64-bit (x86_64), the overflow requires 32-bit
# SSize_t; additionally, no untrusted regex patterns are compiled. No fix
# available in Debian bookworm (requires Perl 5.44+).
CVE-2026-8376

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.5 (Go 1.25.x build): incomplete fix for URL
# escaping inside HTML <meta> tag content attribute - ASCII whitespace around
# '=' bypasses the escaper, leading to XSS. Impact: NONE - rclone does not
# serve HTML or render URLs into HTML templates; it performs outbound R2 bisync
# only. Fix: Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3; rclone upstream has not rebuilt (pinned at
# v1.73.5 for bisync stability).
CVE-2026-39823

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.5 (Go 1.25.x build): ReverseProxy forwards query
# parameters hidden from Rewrite functions when GODEBUG urlmaxqueryparams limit
# is exceeded. Impact: NONE - rclone does not use httputil.ReverseProxy; it is
# an outbound-only CLI tool doing R2 bisync. Fix: Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-39825

# Go stdlib in rclone v1.73.5 (Go 1.25.x build): html/template incorrectly
# escapes <script> blocks when the type attribute is empty or contains ASCII
# whitespace. Impact: NONE - rclone does not use html/template or serve HTML;
# it is an outbound-only CLI tool doing R2 bisync. Fix: Go 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-39826
